=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Prepare the pyrazole branch by N-alkylating 4-bromopyrazole (or a protected equivalent) with 3-halo-N-methylpiperidine to give 1-(1-methylpiperidin-3-yl)-4-bromopyrazole. | Step 2: Convert that aryl bromide to the Suzuki partner by Miyaura borylation, furnishing 1-(1-methylpiperidin-3-yl)-4-(pinacolborane)pyrazole (I2). | Step 3: In parallel, prepare the fused aza-azole core as a regioselective bromo-chloro N-methyl intermediate (I1), e.g. a 7-bromo-4-chloro-1-methyl fused aza-azole, with Br reserved for cross-coupling and the heteroaryl Cl left activated for later SNAr. | Step 4: Couple I1 with boronate I2 under Suzuki conditions to install the pyrazolyl fragment, giving the advanced intermediate 4-chloro-7-[1-(1-methylpiperidin-3-yl)pyrazol-4-yl]-1-methyl-fused aza-azole (I3). | Step 5: React I3 with enantiopure 3-hydroxy-4-methyl-2-pyrrolidinone (I4, C[C@@H]([OH])[C@H]1CNC(=O)C1) under base-promoted SNAr/O-arylation to replace the heteroaryl chloride and deliver the exact target C[C@@H](Oc1nc(-c2cnn(C3CCN(C)CC3)c2)cc2nn(C)cc12)[C@H]1CNC(=O)C1.

